The pro- cedure was the same as that described above, so tfar as the three hearings and following interval were concerned: but the fourth hearing took the simple form of a motion in the comitio tributo for the infliction of a fine on the accused. It was a rogatio of the ordinary legislative kind: the accuser was said irrogare multam.
